cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.DC

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on edge-caching wireless networks and their performance analysis. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper proposes a coded caching strategy and derives the required backhaul and access rates. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper discusses the optimization of system energy efficiency and content delivery time. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a potential category as the paper deals with content data storage and delivery. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also a possible category as the paper involves caching algorithms and optimization problems.
